																		Death to the Prototype
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stormbreath" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3075960); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3075960&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183013" alt="stormbreath" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3075960)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stormbreath" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3075960); return false;" >stormbreath</a></span> <span class="odate time_1529346176 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 Jun 2018 18:22</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3840467">
									

<p>Gear's Proposal is one of my favorite 001 proposals, and I've wanted to write something for it. But the biggest appeal of that article is how mundane and simple it is - how do you honor those original themes of that article?</p>
<p>By killing it off.</p>
<p>At the same time I was getting around to finishing this, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-5968080/magnus-is-holding-a-contest">Magnus's OldCon</a> was ending. I realized that this had something literally dying of old age in it, and a little tweaking of the middle logs solidified the themes of growing old and growing up &#8212; it's not just the Prototype aging here, but the Foundation as a whole.</p>
<p>Thanks to my reviewers:</p>
<ul>
<li>ihp</li>
<li>drblackbox</li>
<li>GrimmCreeper</li>
<li>Stallmantic</li>
<li>Oliver</li>
<li>Voct</li>
</ul>

							</div>

